"Based on the important business logic outlined for the Simple Bookkeeping Application, here are the stored procedures that can be generated to handle the key functionalities:\n\n1. **User Account Management Stored Procedures:**\n   \n   - `usp_CreateUserAccount`\n     - Parameters: @Email (nvarchar), @Password (nvarchar)\n     - Description: Creates a new user account with the provided email address and password.\n\n   - `usp_VerifyUserEmail`\n     - Parameters: @Email (nvarchar)\n     - Description: Verifies the user's email address by confirming the email sent for verification.\n\n   - `usp_UserLogin`\n     - Parameters: @Email (nvarchar), @Password (nvarchar)\n     - Description: Validates user credentials for login and grants access to the application.\n\n2. **Transaction Recording and Categorization Stored Procedures:**\n\n   - `usp_AddTransaction`\n     - Parameters: @UserID (int), @TransactionType (nvarchar), @Amount (decimal), @Date (datetime), @Description (nvarchar), @CategoryID (int)\n     - Description: Adds a new transaction with details like type, amount, date, description, and category to the database.\n\n   - `usp_AddCategory`\n     - Parameters: @UserID (int), @CategoryName (nvarchar)\n     - Description: Allows users to create a new category for organizing transactions.\n\n3. **Financial Summary and Reporting Stored Procedures:**\n\n   - `usp_GetFinancialSummary`\n     - Parameters: @UserID (int)\n     - Description: Retrieves the financial summary including total expenses, total income, and net profit or loss for the user.\n\n   - `usp_GenerateFinancialReport`\n     - Parameters: @UserID (int), @Month (int), @Year (int)\n     - Description: Generates a monthly financial statement/report for the user based on the specified month and year.\n\n4. **Data Backup and Security Stored Procedures:**\n\n   - `usp_BackupUserData`\n     - Parameters: @UserID (int), @BackupMethod (nvarchar)\n     - Description: Initiates the backup process for the user's financial data using the specified method (cloud storage or local backup).\n\n   - `usp_EnsureDataSecurity`\n     - Parameters: @UserID (int)\n     - Description: Implements security measures such as encryption and authentication to protect user financial data.\n\n5. **Mobile Version Access Stored Procedures:**\n\n   - `usp_GetMobileAppData`\n     - Parameters: @UserID (int)\n     - Description: Retrieves necessary data for the mobile application to provide a seamless user experience on mobile devices.\n\n   - `usp_UpdateTransactionMobile`\n     - Parameters: @TransactionID (int), @MobileFlag (bit)\n     - Description: Updates transaction information to reflect changes made through the mobile application.\n\nThese stored procedures will help execute the core functionalities of the Simple Bookkeeping Application efficiently while maintaining data integrity, security, and user experience."